Boulders can be:
- shifted (higher than a 6)
- smashed (higher than a 6), 

Cannot be:
cut, prayed to, etc.

#NUMBER messageDir,SOUTH

#STRING message,"Trust not the gods, different as they are, only two sides of the same coin are unable to meet eye to eye."
Hint Loam Seer can read:
- Have to roll a 5 or above
Success: "Trust not the gods, different as they are, only two sides of the same coin are unable to meet eye to eye."
Failure: (Party member) strained to decipher the meaning to no avail.

#TAG Sign
#NUMBER messageDir,NORTH
#STRING message,"The Nightjar Construction Commitee welcomes you, we apologize if some things aren't working as intended! If this is your first time playing, try these tips:
- Write down all that you learn, you never know what lies between the lines.
- Events utilize certain stats, be mindful of your team.
- The bottom part of the HUD is interactable, try shifting your character marbles around on the overworld and in battle!
- Foes will only challenge you in their arenas, catch them off guard before they outmatch you!

#STRING message,"The Nightjar Construction Committee guide to stats:
HP: Health Points
SP: Skillpoints
DTM: Determination, affects the ease and effectiveness of some actions.
CAM: Camaraderie, affects the ability to perform commanded actions.
SPT: Spirit, affects how high your SP is at the start of each turn."

#TAG Sign

#STRING message,"The Nightjar Construction Committee guide to controls:
Left Click: Confirm/interact with the various interfaces
Enter: Interact using lead party member
Arrow Keys/WASDQE: Move
Spacebar: Toggle action log"

Demo end zone, final encounter/dialogue here

A martialist/possibly unique boss: "Ridiculous, do you not see our poisoned daggers laid at our feet? 
Do you not see the unusual emptiness around you, hear the sounds of laughter as we struggle?
All the same, it is our home you have come to uninvited, it is our kinsmen you cut down.
You shall suffer their fate, not in the name of Mullanginan, but in the name of progress and truth."
- final battle begins, either large group of enemies or miniboss type guy flanked by a few dudes
After martialist/possibly unique boss defeat: "Folly, til the very end, all of you and I both I suppose.
Do what you must, I no longer bear meaning to Telnoth, and neither shall you so long as the two
halves of the whole pull wool over our eyes. Seek the truth. Seek... Selume."
- Demo ends, maybe a congrats screen?
"The night of the poisoned daggers will continue...

Thank you so much if you've made it this far! This is the end of our Dungeon Crawler Jam entry, and 
we hope that you've enjoyed it, feel free to leave feedback and let us know what you thought!"

 on party if user's camaraderie + roll is lower than 8
Event: If lower than 4 is rolled, add enemy to next encounter. If higher, no issue.
Event: Party rolls to sneak past sleeping guard, lower than 6 adds enemy to next encounter
Event: Party rolls to distract guard and sneak past, lower than 8 adds enemy to next encounter
Gate C, locked til correct switch to south is pulled
Locked Door A, opens from opposite side, can be picked if user rolls a perfect 10
Locked Door A, opens from this side
Event: Trap, instigator must exceed 10 on a determination + roll to avoid damage. If not they take 2 points of damage
Switch A and Gate A, teaches players switches open gates sometimes
Lost Haringlee ally, says "No, not this way! We've been pursued, take the long way around, and quickly!"
Event: Roll a perfect 10 or add 3 enemies to the next encounter lol

"...Good, you're from Haringlee. Your welcome to stay, but keep your eyes and
ears open. Mullanginan and his heathen scum are up to something, less scouts 
than usual. The only reason they'd greet us with open arms would be to twist
daggers in our backs."
Event: Roll higher than 5 to avoid adding an enemy to next encounter

Event: Must face the final floor mob, four enemies by default
 added to current pool if it's not empty
"Beware the left hand path, walk it and you will not return whence you came."

Event: An enemy NPC attempts to flee, rolling above 6 instantly smites him and gains an item. 
Rolling lower he escapes and joins the next enemy group
Note: "Footprints end here, but that can't be right? Damn it all, can't let them get the drop on me..."

Event: Forced to encounter an enemy, roll above 4 or two enemies are added to the table
roll above 8 and no enemies are added
Libations, health stuff, stuff to offer to Cherraphy
Enemy roll event, add two if failed
Enemy roll event, add three if failed, add item to inventory if successful
Trap event, low roll is party damage, mid roll is single damage, high is no damage
single enemy event, add one enemy to pool if low roll
add two enemies to pool if low roll
